eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 18 Years
Maximum age: 100 Years
Medically appropriate candidate for radical cystectomy, as per New York University (NYU) attending urologic oncologist

Patients with central nervous system (CNS) involvement may participate if:
* Clinically stable with respect to the CNS tumor at the time of screening and > 4 weeks from prior therapy completion (including radiation and/or surgery) to the start of study treatment
* Not receiving steroid therapy
* Not receiving enzyme inducing anti-epileptic medications that were started for brain metastases (these include carbamazepine, phenytoin, phenobarbital, primidone, oxcarbazepine, topiramate, and vigabatrin)
Patients must have the ability to understand and the willingness to sign a written informed consent document
Creatinine clearance estimated glomerular filtration rate (GFR) >= 30 mL/min/1.73 m^2 (Cockcroft-Gault)
History of allergic reactions attributed to compounds of similar chemical or biologic composition to ibrutinib (difficulty breathing, lip swelling, itching or rash)

groups.description: Patients receive dacarbazine IV over 1-2 hours and bortezomib IV over 3-5 seconds weekly in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (dacarbazine, bortezomib)

groups.description: Patients follow a low ellagitannin diet and receive higher-dose black raspberry confection PO daily for 4-6 weeks and then undergo prostatectomy.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Arm VII (higher-dose black raspberry confection)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Compared using a two-sided paired t-test. Assessed using visual interpretation and semi-quantitative measurements (standardized uptake value [SUV]max, SUVmean, metabolic volume).
outcome_measures.measure: Comparison of uptake of 18FDG between 4D PET/CT and conventional PET/CT for use in radiotherapy planning

outcome_measures.analysis_method: In addition to displaying frequency of adverse events for each grade category, significance of observed differences between treatment arms within each category will be analyzed using Fishers’ exact test.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of adverse events graded according to the active version of CTCAE

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The association between the xerostomia questionnaire and the sialometry at each time point will be assessed graphically. The analysis of the questionnaire and sialometry outcomes will be repeated for the static IMRT results, and posterior distributions of differences between the results will be estimated to describe differences between the outcomes of static and dynamic IMRT treatments.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of xerostomia, measured using the Xerostomia Questionnaire
